description._content: We have fallen in love with Lincolnshire and with so many 1940s events over that way, we get to kill 2 birds with one stone (what an awful saying and where the heck did that originate from?) So having decided to head over for the Lincolnshire Wolds 1940s weekend (see previous blog entry), we decided to have a few days away. I am testing new/old bed in van and this would be perfect opportunity. So van packed, a choice of 40s outfits, we headed about an hour from home to Alkborough. A great little CL on a dairy farm, College Farm. Walks galore from campsite, which take you Alkborough Flats and Julian's Bower turf maze. But we didn't have enough time to explore properly, so we aim to go back for a couple of days. After 40s day, we headed to another CL for night. Nice enough, but not my cup of tea. Did meet this fella though After a hearty breakfast (cereal and fresh pots) we both consulted maps and decided to head to Saltfleet. We found a gorgeous CL called Hilltop Farm, with amazing views and loads of dog walks on the doorstep. Liked it so much decide to stay for 2 nights. First night we took a walk along the 'drainage' ditches and headed to the dunes. The heavens opened and we got soaked. But it was worth it. The doggos loved hunting for critters up and down the dunes. Everyone nicely knackered by time got back to van. Second day we spent 5 hours walking around Saltfleet Haven, beaches and taking in the amazing views. If you looked very carefully, you could see the sea.... miles out . MrRob and doggos stuffed their faces with fish and chips, whilst I could only dream of getting back to my cooking pots and whipping up a gluten free pasta, (making a sauce with some tomatoes we bought from outside a house üòú) If I didn't have to get back for a Doctor's appointment, could easily have stayed a few more days. Lincolnshire has lots to offer. Rest of the photos here (not many this time, I promise) www.flickr.com/photos/bitchinrockmistress/sets/7215771074...
Dog jumping through the fields.

We have fallen in love with Lincolnshire and with so many 1940s events over that way, we get to kill 2 birds with one stone (what an awful saying and where the heck did that originate from?) Secretly, all dogs think their name is "killer". The friendly Goldens, the little Chihuahua's who wear jewelry and have their nails done, each and every doggo. They are mighty hunters, protectors of their hoomans from the evil bunnies and the delivery guy. They know, in their hearts, they are named "killer". And, they would like a biscuit.

Wise words from fellow Red Hatter.
